      • isDesktop

        public boolean isDesktop()
        Indicates if detected user agent data corresponds to a desktop web browser or email client. If true, server should display a typical desktop web UI.
        Returns:
        true if user agent appears to belong to a desktop web browser or email client.

      • isMobile

        public boolean isMobile()
        Indicates if detected user agent data corresponds to a mobile web browser or email client. If true, server should display a UI adapted for small screens like smartphones.
        Returns:
        true if user agent appears to belong to a mobile web browser or email client.

      • isTablet

        public boolean isTablet()
        Indicates if detected user agent data corresponds to a tablet web browser or email client. If true, server should display a UI similar to desktop screens but enhanced for touch event (i.e. having larger buttons, support for touch gestures, etc).
        Returns:
        true if user agent appears to belong to a tablet web browser or email client.

      • isSmartTV

        public boolean isSmartTV()
        Indicates if detected user agent data corresponds to a smart TV. If true, server should display a simple UI ready to be used using a TV remote control.
        Returns:
        true if user agent appears to belong to a TV web browser or email client.

      • isDesktop

        public static boolean isDesktop​(UserAgentType userAgentType,
                                DeviceCategory deviceCategory)
        Indicates if provided user agent type and device category corresponds to a desktop web browser or email client. If true, server should display a typical desktop web UI.
        Parameters:
        userAgentType - user agent type (browser, email client, library, etc).
        deviceCategory - device category (desktop PC, smartphone, tablet, smart TV, game console, etc).
        Returns:
        true if user agent appears to belong to a desktop web browser or email client.
